\textbf{Table of Contents}

\textbf{1. Introduction}


\textbf{1.1 Purpose}

This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) describes the functional
and non-functional requirements for the user-facing side of the Online Learning and Testing System --- a web
application designed to help students practice exams, participate in online courses, and track their academic performance.
Administrative features are specifically excluded from this document's scope.

\textbf{1.2 Project Scope}

The system is a comprehensive educational platform offering the following
core features for users:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Users can register, log in (including Google OAuth), and manage their profiles.
\item
  Users can browse, search, and participate in online courses, as well as access study documents.
\item
  Users can take timed exams (THPT, HSA, TSA) with varied question formats (Multiple Choice, True/False, Fill-in-the-blanks, etc.).
\item
  The system provides real-time exam sessions, automatic grading, detailed result analysis, and leaderboard rankings.
\item
  Users can interact by posting comments on courses, lessons, and exams.
\end{itemize}

