\textbf{B.2 Scope Confirmation}

By signing this document, both parties confirm that:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  The features and requirements described in Sections 1 through 7 of
  this SRS represent the complete and agreed scope of work for this
  project.
\item
  Any feature, behavior, or screen not explicitly described in this
  document is considered out of scope.
\item
  The Client has read and understood the contents of this document,
  including the Out of Scope items listed in Section 7.2.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{B.3 Change Control}

Any change to the scope defined in this SRS --- including adding,
removing, or modifying features --- must follow this process:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Step 1: The requesting party submits a written Change Request
  describing the proposed change.
\item
  Step 2: The Developer provides a written impact assessment (estimated
  time and cost).
\item
  Step 3: Both parties sign a Change Request Addendum before any work on
  the change begins.
\item
  Changes that have not been agreed upon in writing are not binding on
  either party.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{B.4 Acceptance Criteria}

The project will be considered complete and ready for handover when:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  All functional requirements in Section 3 have
  been implemented and are working as described.
\item
  All non-functional requirements in Section 4 have been met to a
  reasonable degree.
\item
  The Client has performed a review and signed the Acceptance section
  (B.5) below.
\end{itemize}

